dataStructure.name: sid.org.tmforum.tip.resource.res.log.tip.nrf.FlowDomain
dataStructure.description:
This object class represents a network grouping of zero or more Matrix Flow Domains (MFDs) and zero or more Connectionless Port Termination Points (CPTPs) that are assigned to these MFDs. See R_TMF518_NRF_I_0049 and R_TMF518_NRF_I_0050.

This entity is optional

This entity is extendable

This entity generates Object Creation notifications

This entity generates Object Deletion notifications

This entity generates Object Discovery notifications

This entity generates Attribute Value Change notifications.
dataStructure.label: FlowDomain

child.name: connectivityState
child.description:
This attribute provides an indication about the server layer connectivity between the Matrix Flow Domains associated to the FlowDomain.

This element is generated from an attribute.

This attribute is optional

This attribute is AVC enabled
child.label: connectivityState

child.name: type
child.description:
This attribute provides an indication of the type of the Flow Domain.

This element is generated from an attribute.

This attribute is invariant

This attribute is optional

This attribute is AVC disabled
child.label: type

child.name: transmissionParameterList
child.description:
This attribute contains the technology-specific parameters associated with the different connectionless layers that are supported by the FD. Refer to to chapter Connectionless Technology Parameters of the attached supporting document SD1-16_LayeredParameters for details of the currently defined Transmission Parameters

This element is generated from an attribute.

This attribute is optional

This attribute is AVC enabled
child.label: transmissionParameterList
